channel.title: PI Webclient Error
channel.description:
Hey well i have made a webclient using a PI Client.
I have tried it myself by going on the website and deleteing my cache then going on the webclient and the cache downloads fine.
But i have told 4 people to try load up the webclient and they all get the same error: 'Error click for details'.
But for me it actualy works and auto-downloads the cache..
What would the problem be?

item.title: PI Webclient Error
item.dc:creator: @Tutorial Tutorial
item.description:
@Tutorial wrote:

[quote=“Ruby Forums Coder, post:5, topic:437505”][quote author=josh124 link=topic=540210.msg3956100#msg3956100 date=1332772750]
Yes haha :’) It’s something to do with the Java.
I’v just deleted JDK1.7 As people say its no good for insidiaX so im installing JDK1.6
[/quote]

I think you need jdk1.6 for running servers underneath 660 revisions, without screwing it up, I could be wrong.[/quote]
Actually, when this happens it is because someone that is using a JDK below version 7 is trying to run a JDK7 compiled client and any other version besides 7 cannot be run with 7+ jarred clients.

Read full topic
